-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
    AND status = 'approved'
```

-- models/marts/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate return rates by product category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.quantity,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
        r.item_id AS returned_item_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE WHEN returned_item_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) AS total_items_returned,
    1.0 * SUM(CASE WHEN returned_item_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity ELSE 0 END) / NULLIF(SUM(quantity), 0) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY category_name
